examples.en: He hunted some, and fished some.
He fished for a coin in his pocket.
Chris fished in his pocket for a coin.
The proof was fished up from some old papers.
She fished around in her purse and pulled out a photo.
They hiked out to a retired beach and fished in the surf.
He fished out a cigar and lighted it with fingers which were trembling.
The paradox is that fishermen would catch more fish if they fished less.
They fished the stream all morning.
